7.  Four-Condition Intersection Structure
The single-channel H+ branch is the intersection of four independent conditions. All four must hold simultaneously. This structure is verified from raw files across all 16 ETGs.
7.1  The four conditions
Condition 1 — Profile family (inner shape geometry)
Organised by (Δ, Q₁₄) where Δ = 1 − Q₁₂ is the half-point unfinished rise and Q₁₄ = B(1/4) is the quarter-point completion. The viable locus: Δ ≈ 0.31–0.46, Q₁₄ ≈ 0.19–0.26.

Condition 2 — Sign gate (inner baryonic amplitude)
Ωᵢⁿ = V̅²ₕₐᵣ(rᵢⁿ) / V²₀̅ₛ(rᵢⁿ) > 1
At fixed profile shape, the sign gate is decided by the absolute inner baryonic normalisation, not profile shape. The NGC3838/NGC3626 control pair demonstrates this directly: near-identical H(y) profiles (H(0.3) = 1.866 for both), but V̅ₕₐᵣ(rᵢⁿ) = 194 vs 284 km/s splits Ωᵢⁿ = 0.705 vs 1.316.

Condition 3 — Inner feasibility (S-threshold)
The completion variable S = Q₁₄ / Δ organises Uₘₐˣ(B): the maximum unfinished-rise level the inner profile can sustain at any kernel width. The log-law:
Uₘₐˣ(B) ≈ 0.2324 − 0.0577 ln(S),   R² = 0.852,   Spearman r(log S, Uₘₐˣ) = −0.982
Threshold: S ≲ 1.70 → inner-feasible (15/16 correct; NGC5582 is the one borderline miss). Single-channel calibrators: S = 0.427, 0.534, 0.829. Inner-infeasible failures: S = 2.37, 6.82, 10.07, 30.63.

Condition 4 — Outer capacity (dynamical load)
u = (V²₀̅ₛ(r₀ᵤₜ) − V̅²ₕₐᵣ(r₀ᵤₜ)) / (Γ₀ r₀ᵤₜ Rₘₐˣ) ≤ 1
u is a dynamical-load variable, not a profile-shape variable. The best simple predictor is X₀ᵤₜ = V²₀̅ₛ(r₀ᵤₜ)/(Γ₀ r₀ᵤₜ), with Pearson r(X₀ᵤₜ, u) = 0.972. Note: u < 1 is NOT equivalent to X₀ᵤₜ < Rₘₐˣ because the baryonic outer term is not negligible (ranges 0.08–1.62 across galaxies).
7.2  Independence of the four axes
The four conditions are genuinely independent. Key cross-correlations: r(Ωᵢⁿ, u) = −0.274, r(S, u) = 0.375, r(log S, u) = 0.515 (all weak). Inner failure is a profile-deformation problem; outer failure is a baryonic-retention problem. They are not the same mechanism.
