12.2  Outer demand isolation: NGC4203 vs NGC3626
Both H+ (Ωᵢⁿ > 1). NGC4203 has collapsed Δ = 0.062 (vs 0.382), Q₁₄ = 0.621 (vs 0.204), S = 10.07 (vs 0.534), back-half overshoot, and u = 1.337 > 1. It is not the same class with bigger u; it is a different structural regime.
